{"source_key":"sha256-784c2f10bfe4a26d66c37ad545f72f01","record_index":880,"record_hash":"sha256:4550ca7d3fd732d4c276a7e78254adb895dedcf8a4aa9b9e3036cb98f68d05f4","timestamp":"2026-05-07T11:37:48.673Z","kind":"message","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:message","role":"user","text":"\n# Review findings:\n\n## Finding 1 (crates/but-capture/src/gitmeta.rs:44-59) [added]\n[P1] Dry-run creates GitMeta state\n\n`Session::open(repo_path)` runs before the dry-run branch, and GitMeta creates/migrates `.git/git-meta.sqlite` on open. That violates the POC contract that `--dry-run` performs no GitMeta writes. Dry-run needs a non-creating read path, or it should treat missing GitMeta state as empty before opening a writable session.\n\n## Finding 2 (crates/but-capture/src/gitmeta.rs:105-118) [added]\n[P2] Deduplicate duplicate records within one capture\n\nThe write plan checks records only against persisted hash sets, not hashes already selected during this run. A transcript containing the same trimmed JSONL record twice will overcount `recordsNew` and append duplicate transcript envelopes. Clone the hash sets into mutable planned sets and insert as each record is accepted.\n\n## Finding 3 (crates/but-capture/src/gitmeta.rs:64-77) [added]\n[P2] Transcript append can duplicate after partial failure\n\nThe transcript envelope is appended before `transcript-record-hashes` is updated. If capture exits or `set_add` fails after `list_push`, a later capture can append the same envelope again. Either make the list/hash update atomic through GitMeta if possible, or rebuild transcript hashes from existing envelope records before planning appends.\n\n## Finding 4 (crates/but-capture/src/capture.rs:107-108) [added]\n[P2] Path identity uses lossy UTF-8\n\nThe canonical transcript path is converted with `to_string_lossy()` and then used as the fallback session-key hash input. Distinct non-UTF-8 paths can collapse to the same replacement-character string. Hash platform-native path bytes for identity, and use lossy text only for storage/display if needed.\n\n## Finding 5 (crates/but/src/lib.rs:270-280) [added]\n[P2] `--status-after` is accepted but ignored\n\nThe global `--status-after` flag is accepted for `agent-session capture`, but this command returns a bare capture report instead of the CLI's documented `{ result, status }` JSON wrapper for mutation commands. Either wire the normal status-after path or explicitly reject/status-disable it for this hidden command.\n\n## Finding 6 (crates/but-capture/src/transcript.rs:94-95) [added]\n[P3] Preserve `payload.type` in event kind\n\nThe POC contract says event kind should use top-level `type` plus `payload.type` when present, but normalization currently stores only top-level `type`. Include `payload.type` for records such as `event_msg` while preserving the existing fallback.\n\n## Finding 7 (crates/but/src/args/agent_session.rs:22-24) [added]\n[P3] `--include-transcript` help omits local-only storage warning\n\nThe help text warns that transcripts can contain sensitive data, but the contract also requires warning that POC storage is local-only. Add that sentence to the option help.\n\n## My request for Codex:\nlets fix all of these\n","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-07T11:37:48.673Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"message","role":"user","content":[{"type":"input_text","text":"\n# Review findings:\n\n## Finding 1 (crates/but-capture/src/gitmeta.rs:44-59) [added]\n[P1] Dry-run creates GitMeta state\n\n`Session::open(repo_path)` runs before the dry-run branch, and GitMeta creates/migrates `.git/git-meta.sqlite` on open. That violates the POC contract that `--dry-run` performs no GitMeta writes. Dry-run needs a non-creating read path, or it should treat missing GitMeta state as empty before opening a writable session.\n\n## Finding 2 (crates/but-capture/src/gitmeta.rs:105-118) [added]\n[P2] Deduplicate duplicate records within one capture\n\nThe write plan checks records only against persisted hash sets, not hashes already selected during this run. A transcript containing the same trimmed JSONL record twice will overcount `recordsNew` and append duplicate transcript envelopes. Clone the hash sets into mutable planned sets and insert as each record is accepted.\n\n## Finding 3 (crates/but-capture/src/gitmeta.rs:64-77) [added]\n[P2] Transcript append can duplicate after partial failure\n\nThe transcript envelope is appended before `transcript-record-hashes` is updated. If capture exits or `set_add` fails after `list_push`, a later capture can append the same envelope again. Either make the list/hash update atomic through GitMeta if possible, or rebuild transcript hashes from existing envelope records before planning appends.\n\n## Finding 4 (crates/but-capture/src/capture.rs:107-108) [added]\n[P2] Path identity uses lossy UTF-8\n\nThe canonical transcript path is converted with `to_string_lossy()` and then used as the fallback session-key hash input. Distinct non-UTF-8 paths can collapse to the same replacement-character string. Hash platform-native path bytes for identity, and use lossy text only for storage/display if needed.\n\n## Finding 5 (crates/but/src/lib.rs:270-280) [added]\n[P2] `--status-after` is accepted but ignored\n\nThe global `--status-after` flag is accepted for `agent-session capture`, but this command returns a bare capture report instead of the CLI's documented `{ result, status }` JSON wrapper for mutation commands. Either wire the normal status-after path or explicitly reject/status-disable it for this hidden command.\n\n## Finding 6 (crates/but-capture/src/transcript.rs:94-95) [added]\n[P3] Preserve `payload.type` in event kind\n\nThe POC contract says event kind should use top-level `type` plus `payload.type` when present, but normalization currently stores only top-level `type`. Include `payload.type` for records such as `event_msg` while preserving the existing fallback.\n\n## Finding 